New Records: Victor Wembanyama scored 29 points, 10-17 from the field, 7 rebounds, and 3 blocks.
San Antonio Spurs outrebounded Houston Rockets 57-46.
Key Match Events: Houston Rockets made a 21-8 run in the fourth quarter.
Jalen Green scored 27 points for Houston.
Victor Wembanyama made alley-oop dunks with assists from Chris Paul.
Post-Match Reflections: San Antonio coach Gregg Popovich emphasized the need for physicality.
Houston Rockets struggled in the first half but finished strong.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was the home opener for San Antonio Spurs.
The Rockets and Spurs will face off again on Monday.
